Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component caas-core
Version r_4.0.0_146
Scrum Metadata :  

From Perf: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space.
 - No Config Changes

 - DB chgs

Component Release Info for Sprint Whoopie!:

Release of Component Dynamic-Ad-Insertion-cm
Version r_4.0.0_255

Scrum Metadata :  
Joel:
This build includes the ability to create and edit Campaign Line Items in a tabular workflow.  The workflow does not include Metadata targeting, Daypart scheduling, Break/Position, Goal Allocation, or Billing.  User can include Basic Line Item settings (status, start/end dates, label, priority/value, network, goal strategy, goal quantity, trick mode enable/disable, placement pref), Campaign Item Media Assets, and Product Category Separation, including Category Exclusions.

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component Dynamic-Ad-Insertion-cm
Version r_4.0.0_322

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space.

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component dai-cip
Version r_4.0.0_209

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space. 


 - No Config Changes



 - No DB Changes

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component Pgmr-Cpgn-Int
Version r_4.0.0_199

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space.

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component MicroDev
Version r_4.0.0_150

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space.

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component ads-core
Version r_4.0.0_100

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space.

Component Release Info for Sprint Mammoth:

Release of Component Dynamic-Ad-Insertion-engine
Version r_4.0.0_387

Scrum Metadata :  
From Performance: Placement Limitation features seemed to have not introduced any performance impact to any of our application areas. Due to the rush in turning the Placement Limitation features over to Prod, completion of the Metadata Publisher and NCIS test plans are not as complete as desired. This will be continued over the next week. 
 
Testing explicit placement limitation rules in Freewheel CIPs is also outstanding in testing. We need to revise our CIP generator to include these rules in the CIP.  We tested the rule defaults only. Kassi is integration testing this with Freewheel starting this week, so we will be working this angle as well in parallel. 
 
Reasonable disk space or log rotation schedules will need to allocated to the NCIS and MetaData Publisher server instances. Not sure what the prescribed frequency the CRON jobs here will be but messages sent are large and can eat up a lot of logging disk space. 


 - No Config Changes



 - No DB Changes
